<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Hermes&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Overview">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Overview">Overview</span></h2>
<p>The <b>Hermes</b> is similar to the <a href="/index.php/Boron" title="Boron">Boron</a> <a href="/index.php/Manta" title="Manta">Manta</a>, trading a little speed for much improved defensive capability.
</p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Hermes&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Background">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Background">Background</span></h2>
<p>The Hermes is based on an old original design for the Ganymede, but the design was reworked to accommodate passengers.  Like most <a href="/index.php/Paranid" title="Paranid">Paranid</a> ships it is able to hold a certain amount of weaponry, primarily for defense.  It is very unlikely you will see this ship in <a href="/index.php/Argon" title="Argon">Argon</a> systems, mainly because the tension between the two neighbors remains high.
</p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Hermes&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: Physical Characteristics">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Physical_Characteristics">Physical Characteristics</span></h2>
<p>Like most <a href="/index.php/Commonwealth" title="Commonwealth">Commonwealth</a> <a href="/index.php/TP" title="TP">TPs</a>, the Hermes is a variation on the race's <a href="/index.php/TS" title="TS">TS</a> model, in this case the <a href="/index.php/Demeter" title="Demeter">Demeter</a>.  The modular cargo section is replaced with a passenger section.
</p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Hermes&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: Variants">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Variants">Variants</span></h2>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Hermes&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section: Hermes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Hermes">Hermes</span></h3>
<p>Not featuring any fancy title, the basic version of the ship is the standard by which other variants are measured.
</p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Hermes&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6" title="Edit section: Hermes Hauler">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Hermes_Hauler">Hermes Hauler</span></h3>
<p>Hauler variants of ships tend to have larger cargobays and sometimes tougher defences, trading off offensive combat attributes.
</p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Hermes&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: Combat">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Combat"> Combat </span></h2>
<p>The Hermes is less helpless in a fight than some other TP-class ships, but it is still a TP and should not be allowed into a firefight lightly.
</p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Hermes&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: Equipment">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Equipment"> Equipment </span></h2>
<table bgcolor="white" align="center" style="border-style:dotted;border-width:2px;margin-top:5px;border-color:#aaaaaa">
<tr>
<td><i>This section is a <a href="/index.php/X3_Wiki:Stub" title="X3 Wiki:Stub">stub</a>. You can help us by <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://x3wiki.com/index.php?title=Hermes&amp;action=edit">expanding it</a>.</i>
</td></tr></table>
<p><br />
</p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/index.php?title=Hermes&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: Availability">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Availability"> Availability </span></h2>
<p>At least one Hermes variant is available at most <a href="/index.php/Paranid_Shipyard" title="Paranid Shipyard">Paranid Shipyards</a>.
</p>
